        Dining table / contemporary / glass / steel

            FILO by David Lòpez Quincoces        
LEMA Home















Dining table / contemporary / glass / steel

                                                                    - FILO by David Lòpez Quincoces                                                            
















































        Characteristics    



Type: 
dining


Style: 
contemporary


Material: 
glass, steel




Shape: 
rectangular, square


Height: 

                            72 cm (28.35 in)                        


Length: 

                            140 cm (55.12 in), 180 cm (70.87 in), 240 cm (94.49 in)                        




Width: 

                            140 cm (55.12 in), 180 cm (70.87 in), 100 cm (39.37 in)                        




        Description    


A rigorous and elegant design for Filo table by David Lòpez Quincoces made of thin steel legs welded to a frame of the same material, which confer ultra-lightness to the structure. Within this gentle frame, a top in cement completes the sculptural and hieratic line of this piece. Its essential lines fit different rooms perfectly, making it suitable as dining table and also as desk.

STRUCTURE:
-Metal
COUNTERS:
-Cement




                Go to the LEMA Home website for more information            


